<br />
Hehe.  Us old-school mages who NEVER had a pet health window used to have /pet health HOTKEYED!  It was the thing we were hitting every 10 seconds (or less) to see how much health our pet actually had!  Only later they added the ability to see buffs, and we were all like "wow!  cool!  I can actually tell when burnout wears off without needing a stopwatch!"
<br />

<br />
SO many conveniences today.  They don't change the game balance, but merely make it a LOT less of a PITA to play.
<br />

<br />
I agree that they need more filtering options.  The "my spells" filter has NEVER worked right.  I would like to see all MY stuff, but none of anybody else's, but you ALWAYS see other people's spells too.  So it is all screwed up.  They really need to work on them.  What they have done so far is good, but it definitely needs some work.  I didn't know about the bard song issue (I don't have pet affinity yet), but I can see how annoying it would be.  Definitely something that needs to be looked at.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
